Description: Facilities for async programming and communication in Clojure
Vulnerability: In Async before 2.6.4 and 3.x before 3.2.2, a malicious user can obtain privileges via the mapValues() method, aka lib/internal/iterator.js createObjectIterator prototype pollution.

Description: General data-binding functionality for Jackson: works on core streaming API
Vulnerability: jackson-databind before 2.13.0 allows a Java StackOverflow exception and denial of service via a large depth of nested objects.
